// Regression: quit inside a user-defined function must terminate
// the program immediately, not just return to the caller. In heap
// mode, RETURN only returns to the caller; without the sentinel
// propagation fix, quit corrupts the heap stack pointer.
//
// The recursive `counter` function forces heap mode. `do_quit`
// calls quit from inside a function. 99 print must never execute.
: dup 1 pick ;
: noop ;
: do_quit quit ;
: counter dup 0 swap < if go else noop ;
: go dup 1 - counter drop ;
42 print
do_quit
99 print
